# PRD to Issues —

## One-time label setup

Run once per repo to enable label-based filtering. Agents can then use `label:afk` to identify tickets they're allowed to pick up autonomously.

```bash
gh label create "vertical-slice" --color "0075ca" --description "Created by prd-to-issues skill"
gh label create "afk" --color "2ea44f" --description "Can be implemented autonomously, no human review needed"
gh label create "hitl" --color "e4e669" --description "Requires human decision or review before progressing"
gh label create "blocked" --color "d93f0b" --description "Has unresolved blockers"
```

If labels already exist in the repo, skip any that conflict. The skill will apply labels where available and skip gracefully where not.

---

## Issue body template

```md
## Parent PRD
#<prd-issue-number>

## What to build

A concise description of this vertical slice. Describe the end-to-end behavior, not layer-by-layer
implementation. Reference specific sections of the parent PRD rather than duplicating content.

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] Criterion 1
- [ ] Criterion 2
- [ ] Criterion 3

## Blocked by

- Blocked by #<issue-number>

Or: "None — can start immediately"

## User stories addressed

Reference by number from the parent PRD:
- User story 3
- User story 7
```

---

## HITL vs AFK decision guide

| Scenario | Classification |
|---|---|
| Architectural decision needs human sign-off | HITL |
| External design review or stakeholder approval required | HITL |
| Pure implementation with clear acceptance criteria | AFK |
| Schema migration with no ambiguity | AFK |
| New endpoint following established patterns | AFK |
| First endpoint establishing a new pattern | HITL |
| Ambiguous requirement needing clarification | HITL |
